				<div class="row">
					<div class="col">
						<hr><h3>ABOUT THE HOSTEL</h3>
						<hr>
						<p style="letter-spacing: 1px">C-DAC, Kharghar has its own hostel inside the campus at
							kharghar,mumbai. There are two separate but interconnected wings
							for boys and girls each having 50 twin sharing spacious rooms
							with air-conditioned dining hall and other modern amenities to
							ensure comfortable stay of the students.</p>
					</div>
				</div>


				<div class="row">
					<div class="col">
						<hr><h3>ALLOTMENT OF HOSTEL</h3>
						<hr>
						<p  style="letter-spacing: 1px">
							Allotment of hostel will be done on first-cum-first-serve basis
							only. <br> 1. Online application for admission in the Hostel
							in the prescribed format is available on the official website of
							CDAC, Kharghar (www.cdac.in). <br> 2.Online application for
							the hostel accommodation shall be treated as valid only after
							taking the admission in concern programme. No application shall
							be treated as valid those students will apply before taking the
							admission in the courses. <br> 3. Students, whose parents
							are staying in NCR will not be given accommodation in the hostel.
							<br> 4. The list of students who will eligible to take the
							admission in the hostel on first-cumfirst-serve basis will be
							displayed on CDAC, Kharghar's website before commencing the
							programme. <br> 5. The applicant has to take admission by
							the given due date, failing which his/her seat will be allotted
							to the next student. <br> The decision of the Executive
							Director, C-DAC, Kharghar regarding admission to the hostel shall
							be final.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>


				<div class="row">
					<div class="col">
						<hr><h3>INVENTORY</h3>
						<hr>
						<p  style="letter-spacing: 1px">Each resident shall be provided with one table, chair, cot
							with mattress, and one almirah/shelf and serviceable electrical
							light fitting/fixtures. At the time of allotting the rooms, the
							resident shall be required to sign the inventory list and the
							declaration attached there to.</p>
					</div>
				</div>



				<div class="row">
					<div class="col">
						<hr><h3>FEE STRUCTURE</h3>
						<hr>
						<p  style="letter-spacing: 1px">
							One month to six month duration<br>
							<br> Room Charges per month Rs. 4,000/-<br> Mess
							Charges per month Rs. 4,000/-*<br> Security Deposit
							(refundable) Rs. 8,000/-@ <br> <b>The Executive
								Director, C-DAC, kharghar is empowered to revise the fee from
								time to time and such revisions shall be binding on all
								residents.</b>
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="row">
					<div class="col">
						<hr><h3>CANCELLATION OF ADMISSION</h3>
						<hr>
						<p  style="letter-spacing: 1px">
							Admission shall be cancelled and resident has to evict from the
							Hostel if he/she is found to be indulging in any of the following
							acts:<br> i) Unruly behavior in hostel or the Institute
							premises<br> ii) Keeping guests without permission<br>
							iii) Anti-social activities<br> iv) Mischief causing damage
							to the hostel property.<br> v) Ceases to be a student of
							C-DAC, kharghar.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="row">
					<div class="col">
						<hr><h3>RULES AND REGULATIONS</h3>
						<hr>
						<p  style="letter-spacing: 1px">
							The hostel residents are advised to strictly adhere to the
							following rules and regulations: General Information 1) The
							hostel resident are required to provide names, addresses, contact
							numbers along with latest photographs of his/her parents and
							local guardians in hostel admission form. The students will be
							allowed to go out of the hostel with a written request from their
							parents/declared local guardians, to the full satisfaction of the
							authorities.<br> 2) All students who are allotted room in
							the hostel shall be required to obtain valid Identity Card from
							C-DAC, kharghar and will show the same for gaining access to the
							hostel premises.<br> 3) All the students must submit a fresh
							declaration about their home address at the beginning of each
							academic year session.<br> 4) In case Hosteller’s parents
							change their residence the same should be intimated within a week
							to the Hostel office in writing. <br> 5) Residents are
							advised to adhere to the fees payment schedule issued by the
							hostel Administration, failing which late payment fee @Rs.50/-
							for each day shall be charged.<br> 6) Female residents are
							strictly prohibited to enter the Boys Block. Similarly, male
							residents are also strictly prohibited to enter the Girls Block.
							Any violation in this regard shall be a fit and cogent ground for
							evicting the resident from the hostel and rusticating him/her
							from the institute, without any notice.<br> 7) All residents
							are required to apply in writing and obtain prior permission
							before leaving the hostel during vacation/holidays.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>


				<div class="row">
					<div class="col">
						<hr><h3>Discipline</h3>
						<hr>
						<p  style="letter-spacing: 1px">
							1) Ragging in the hostel/institute premises is unlawful. Any
							resident found indulging in such activities may be handed over to
							the Police, apart from rustication from the institute.<br>
							2) The common room facility will be there only upto 10:00pm.<br>
							3) Day scholars are not allowed to go to student’s wing. If any
							day scholar is found visiting a hostel room the resident of that
							room who allows him/her to visit him/her shall invite
							disciplinary action.<br> 4) Every student is responsible for
							the care of the room and its furnishing allotted to him/her and
							the furniture provided to him/her. No furniture will be removed
							from the room. Similarly no additional furniture will be brought
							into the room without prior permission of the warden. Charges
							will be recovered for all damages and losses caused by resident.<br>
							5) Residents are required to maintain cleanliness within the
							premises, toilets, common spaces, lawns and adjoining areas of
							the Hostel. Photographs pictures etc. shall not be pasted or
							displayed on the walls of the room/corridor. <br> 6) Any
							forbidden articles such as heaters, immersion rods, irons,
							stoves, electric kettle etc, if found in the room will be
							confiscated and in addition a fine of at least Rs.1000/- may be
							imposed for the violation of the rule. The decision of the
							warden/inspection committee will be final in this regard.<br>
							7) Residents, at all times, are expected to conduct themselves
							well with regard to the comfort and convenience of other
							residents. No resident is allowed to indulge in any activity in
							his/her room/premises, which may cause disturbance to others.<br>
							8) Music system may be played at low volume in rooms if neighbors
							and roommates do not object. Any violation of these regulations
							will lead to confiscation of these articles.<br> 9) Every
							student, on going out of his/her room, shall switch off the light
							and fan.<br> 10) Smoking, chewing tobacco, consuming
							alcoholic drinks or any other intoxicating drugs etc. are
							strictly prohibited. Any Residents, found indulging in such
							practices, shall be asked to vacate the hostel, forfeiting the
							hostel charges already paid.<br> 11) No resident who have
							taken any alcoholic drinks/ drugs even outside hostel shall be
							allowed to enter the hostel.<br> 12) Residents shall not
							conduct group meetings; organize parties or get-together inside
							the hostel premises.<br> 13) Residents are advised not to
							keep valuables in their rooms. Management shall not be
							responsible for any loss.<br> 14) No resident is allowed to
							go out of the hostel after 8:00pm. Violation of this rule would
							lead to disciplinary action. <br>
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="row">
					<div class="col">
						<hr><h3>Leave</h3><hr>
						
						<p  style="letter-spacing: 1px">
							Students will be given permission to leave the hostel for night
							out by the warden provided his/her application has been forwarded
							by HOD after proper verification from parents/already declared
							local guardian(s).<br> Applications for night out must be
							submitted to the warden at least 24 hours before the leave asked
							for duly verified by the HOD after proper verification from
							parents/already declared local guardian(s). Administration has a
							right to ask the students to get a written verification from the
							parents/local guardians allowing him/her for night out <br>
							<br>
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>


